cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the recognition of temporal expressions in Polish language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of Bidirectional Long-Short Term Memory (BiLSTM) network with additional CRF layer, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL). Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in NLP and ML. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. The paper also involves experiments and evaluation, which can be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
